@node EXPBOARDS "JV-1080/Expansion Boards"

Currently supported expansion boards:

 SR-JV80-01 Pop            
 SR-JV80-02 Orchestral     
 SR-JV80-03 Piano          
 SR-JV80-04 Vintage        
 SR-JV80-05 World          
 SR-JV80-06 Dance          
 SR-JV80-07 Super Sound Set
 SR-JV80-08 60's and 70's Keyboards
  
If you have another expansion board it is quite easy (although tedious)
to add support for that one too!

Take a look at the file "Exp.Orchestral". It's a normal ASCII text file. 
It contains all the waveforms for the Orchestral board. If you have, 
let's say, the Dance expansion board you create a file called Exp.<name> 
where <name> is the name you want to use in the wave window's waveform 
selection gadget.

The first line must have a special format:

WAVES <#waves> <ID>

The <#waves> is simply the number of waveforms in the expansion board.
The <ID> is the number of the expansion board. Ex. Piano is #3..

The rest of the file is the waveform names. The first character can
be either 'L', 'O', 'M'. Looping, Oneshot or Menu. If you don't know
what type a waveform is type '-'

Happy typing! :)

If you create a new expansion board file please send it to me so that
I can add it for the next release. You will of course be credited :)

@endnode

@node ENVELOPE "JV-1080/Envelope Editor"

The TVA, TVF and Pitch windows features a special gadget: @{b}The envelope
gadget@{ub}. This gadget allows you to edit an envelope graphically with
your mouse.

@{u}How does it work?@{uu}
If you click the left mouse button over one of the knobs (and keep it
pressed you can drag the knob around). This works in the same way
as dragging icons on the Workbench.

You can fine-adjust a knob by clicking outside the knob. Clicking to the
left will move the knob left by 1. Clicking above the knob will move the
knob up by 1 etc. etc..

@endnode

@node HISTORY "JV-1080/History"

 Program history - a description of each release. Note: I use
 Commodores (RIP) definition of version numbers. Ex. 1.10 is newer 
 than 1.5!

 In fact every time I make a change in the sourcecode and I compile
 this PlugIn the version number gets increased by one!

 I use the following 3 letter IDs to describe changes:

   FIX - Bug fix
   NEW - New feature
   CHG - Change in behaviour from previous versions

 @{u}History (Newest on top)@{uu}

 @{b}v1.347 - 25-Jul-1999@{ub}
  · NEW. Random LFO generation
  · CHG. Updated internal tables for random patch generation
  · FIX. When generating a random patch it is automatically sent to the JV-1080.
  · FIX. Random data is only generated for the active and selected tones.
  · FIX. Fixed another bug in the wave window when selecting waves from 
         expansion boards.
  · NEW. Random patch generation.
  · NEW. Now the envelope gadget is a 'real' MUI custom class meaning that
         it has its own preferences in the MUI-prefs program.

 @{b}v1.320 - 24-Mar-1998@{ub}
  · FIX. The Install script no longer installs the Install script itself.
  · FIX. Trailing spaces in patch names received from the JV-1080 are 
         now stripped.
  · FIX. Fixed even more bugs in the wave-window when selecting waveforms.
         Should finally work perfectly now :-)
  · FIX. Fixed some bugs in the wave window that caused problems when
         selecting waves if you were editing several tones at once.
  · NEW. Visual indication on knobs when grabbing them..
  · NEW. The knobs in the envelope gadget are not drawn on top of 
         each other when their time value is zero.
  · FIX. Removed some of the 'snapping' that could occur when grabbing
         a knob in the envelope gadget.
  · FIX. When editing several tones at once using the Wave window all your
         changes will now be updated via MIDI instead of just the current 
         tone.
  · FIX. When selecting a wave for a Tone the patch wasn't marked as 
         changed.
  · FIX. Pressing the "Store Current" button in the patchbank window
         with no selected entries caused a crash.
  · CHG. You cannot save an empty patchbank anymore..
  · NEW. New file format for patchbanks. Now only patches actually used
         will be saved. Saves a lot of disk space if you have banks with
         few patches. Patchbank files in the old format can still be
         loaded.
  · FIX. When receiving patches from the patchbank window any trailing
         spaces in the patch names will be removed.
  · FIX. Fixed bugs in Wave editor when selecting waveforms from an
         expansion module. (and when receiving patches using waveforms
         from an expansion module)
  · FIX. Fixed some wrong Loop/Oneshot on waveforms for the Vintage 
         expansion module. (thanks Simon!)

 @{b}v1.238 - 2 Sep 1996@{ub}
  · FIX. Envelopes: It was possible to fine adjust the level of the last 
         knob in the TVA window..
  · NEW. Envelopes: Visual indicator of which knob you're adjusting. The
         corresponding text gadget will light up.

 @{b}v1.237 - 21 Jul 1996@{ub}
  · FIX. The "levels" in the pitch envelope now has a max of +63 instead
         of +64 (which of course caused the JV-1080 to complain).
  · NEW. You can now remove more than one patch at a time in the patch
         bank window.
  · NEW. Patch Bank window has multi-patch-save if more than one patch 
         is selected.
  · NEW. Loading of patches now supports multi-selection! Both the main
         window and the patch bank window
  · FIX. If you played around with MUI-prefs and then tried to use a
         filerequester things would blow up!
  · FIX. If you deleted expansion boards in the prefs window they didn't
         disappear for real - it only looked that way!
  · NEW. Added some more gadget-help texts. Thanks Jan!
  · NEW. New layout in tone select window. Horizontally placed
         selection buttons just like on the JV-1080 itself and
         gives the window a bigger dragbar as a side effect.
  · NEW. You can now drag patches from the patch bank window to the
         patch list (main) window. Only one at a time though :-\
  · NEW. You can now rename patches in the patch bank window. Double
         click on an entry and a window pops up..
  · NEW. Hotkey on the "Remove" button in the patch bank window.
  
 @{b}v1.178 - 18 Jun 1996@{ub}
  · NEW. Added waveform files for 4 more expansion boards.
  · NEW. Envelope-value readouts in Pitch, TVA and TVF windows.
  · NEW. New window just for selecting which Tone you are looking at and
         which Tones will be affected by changes. You can now edit ex.
         Tone #1 and Tone #3 at the same time.
  · CHG. The fade-mode selector in the LFO window is now a cycle gadget
         instead of a slider
  · FIX. There was some empty space at the top of the "misc" group in
         the LFO window. Removed..
  · NEW. Waveform names for the "Dance Expansion module" included.

  @{b}v1.130 - 26 May 1996@{ub}
  · FIX. Fixed the MIDI updating on envelopes when fine adjusting knobs.
  · FIX. The TVA and TVF envelopes now starts at the bottom instead of
         at the middle of the envelope..
  · NEW. The TVF and Pitch envelopes now have a horizontal line at the
         very end of the envelope..
  · FIX. When receiving a patch the name of the patch in the Main Window
         and the Patch Common window wasn't updated..

  @{b}v1.125 - 10 May 1996@{ub}
  · NEW. Graphical editing of envelopes
  · CHG. Moved some gadget-groups around in the LFO window
  · FIX. Moving some sliders in the ToneCtrl window didn't mark the
         patch as changed.
  · NEW. Some more error requesters in program, mostly to
         support the fact that Apache not necessarely owns the MIDI port
  · NEW. Error requesters instead of printing to console (normal window)
  · CHG. Print stuff in the menu removed
  · NEW. Some internal changes to support the changes in the 
         Apache/PlugIn communication scheme.
  · NEW. This PlugIn will now ask user about quitting if user tried
         to quit Apache instead of just quitting the PlugIn.
  · CHG. The main window is now the last one to open.

  @{b}v1.19 - 2 Apr 1996@{ub}
  · NEW. Compiled for 68000 instead of 68020
  · NEW. Waveform list for the Vintage expansion board
  · NEW. Drag'n'drop between entries in the patch bank window
  · NEW. Drag'n'drop from main window to patch bank window
  · CHG. Main window will always be the active one at startup

  @{b}v1.0 - 17 Mar 1996@{ub}
    First release.
    
@endnode

